com.ibm.portal.portlet.service.credentialvault.credentials
Interface SSMTokenCredential

All Superinterfaces:
ActiveCredential, Credential, JaasSubjectCredential
All Known Implementing Classes:
SSMTokenCredential
Deprecated. Since 8.5. 

public interface SSMTokenCredential
extends JaasSubjectCredential

Credential for authenticating at a back-end system that is within the same Openwave SSM SSO-Domain as the portal, i.e. you are using an Openwave SSM authentication proxy for the portal authentiation. The credential needs to be provided in form of the portal's JAAS Subject, containing a private credential that holds the user's SSMCredential. To be used in following way:

  1. Construct (initialize) the credential
  2. Pass an Http URL connection to the credential in order to add the SSMCredential to the request header ("getAuthenticatedConnection")
  3. If necessary, set aditional HTTP headers
  4. Send the request
Preconditions:
  • The configuration data passed to the init method must define the values that are required by JaasSubjectCredential
Assumptions:
  • If the Url uses SSL (https://) the JSSE has already been registered

Since:
5.1.0.1
